{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"lookupCertificateIssuer","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"TLSCertificateT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"certificate"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"TLSCertificateT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"interaction","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSInteractionRef","text":"TLSInteractionRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO17TLSInteractionRefV"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"flags"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@EA@GTlsDatabaseLookupFlags","text":"GTlsDatabaseLookupFlags"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO17TLSCertificateRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSCertificateRef","text":"TLSCertificateRef"},{"text":"! ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TLSCertificateT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"text":"TLSCertificateProtocol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSCertificateProtocol","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO22TLSCertificateProtocolP"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function can block. Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_tls_database_lookup_certificate_issuer_async()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to perform the lookup operation asynchronously.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Beware this function cannot be used to build certification paths. The","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"issuer certificate returned by this function may not be the same as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the certificate that would actually be used to construct a valid","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"certification path during certificate verification."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/datatracker.ietf.org\/doc\/html\/rfc4158","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" explains"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"why an issuer certificate cannot be naively assumed to be part of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the certification path (though GLib’s TLS backends may not follow the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"path building strategies outlined in this RFC). Due to the complexity"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of certification path building, GLib does not provide any way to know"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"which certification path will actually be used when verifying a TLS","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"certificate. Accordingly, this function cannot be used to make"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"security-related decisions. Only GLib itself should make security","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"decisions about TLS certificates."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSDatabaseProtocol\/lookupCertificateIssuer(certificate:interaction:flags:cancellable:)-